Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unspecifyBlackBox(25.10)                              unspecifyBlackBox(25.10)

Name
       unspecifyBlackBox  -  Unspecifies or deletes a blackbox and converts it
       to a module if the blackbox was originally defined as a  module,  or  a
       block if the blackbox has a cdump or LEF macro definition

Syntax
       unspecifyBlackBox

       [-help]

       {-cell <cellName> | -all}

       [-keepPtn]

       Unspecifies  or  deletes  a blackbox and converts it to a module if the
       blackbox was originally defined as a module, or a block if the blackbox
       has a cdump or LEF macro definition. You can use this command after im-
       porting the design.

       Note: You cannot delete a blackbox of an undefined module or cell.

Parameters
       -all   Selects all blackboxes for deletion.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell <cellname>
              Selects an individual blackbox for deletion. You can  use  wild-
              cards (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each unspecifyBlackBox parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man unspecifyBlackBox

       -keepPtn
              Preserves  the  partition  information. You should only use this
              option if the blackbox is placed inside the core area and is de-
              fined as a module in the netlist.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command deletes all blackboxes that  begin  with
                the  letter A-some of which are inside the core area, and some
                which are outside the core area and converts them to either  a
                fence or module.

                unspecifyBlackBox -cell A*

Related Information
              * specifyBlackBox

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

